title GoF - Behavior #04 - Iterator

interface Aggregate {
    +create_iterator()
}

class ConcreteAggregate {
    +create_iterator()
}

Aggregate <|.. ConcreteAggregate

interface Iterator {
    +first()
    +next()
    +is_done()
    +current_item()
}

note right of Iterator::first
    sets current to the first item
end note
note right of Iterator::next
    advances current to the next item
end note
note right of Iterator::is_done
    returns true if current is beyond the end of the collection
end note
note right of Iterator::current_item
    returns the current item
end note

class ConcreteIterator {
    -aggregate : ConcreteAggregate
    -current : int
    +first()
    +next()
    +is_done()
    +current_item()
}

Iterator <|.. ConcreteIterator

ConcreteAggregate ..> ConcreteIterator
ConcreteIterator --> ConcreteAggregate

@enduml
